    <stitle>5 SPEED AND 6 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>INPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front bearing bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302611">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302611" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302611" filename="../figg13/g1302611.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Remove Front Bearing Bolts and Jar Front Bearing Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Jar the front bearing cover with a rubber mallet (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302611">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the oil seal. Remove the oil seal if damaged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302612">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302612" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302612" filename="../figg13/g1302612.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Inspect Oil Seal</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the input shaft assembly from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302613">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302613" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302613" filename="../figg13/g1302613.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Remove Input Shaft Assembly From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a chisel and hammer to remove the bearing cage and rollers from the input shaft assembly
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302614">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302614" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302614" filename="../figg13/g1302614.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove Bearing Cage and Rollers, and Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a bearing puller to remove the bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302614">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">For the FS-5205 model, if necessary, remove the retention snap ring and the bearing
                retention ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302615">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Remove the fourteen (14) roller bearings from the main
                drive gear bearing pocket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302616">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302615" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302615" filename="../figg13/g1302615.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Remove Retention Snap Ring and Bearing Retention Ring</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="f1302616" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302616" filename="../figg13/g1302616.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Remove Roller Bearings From Main Drive Gear Bearing Pocket</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
